title: 2022 Pokemon Japanese SWSH Star Birth Charizard V #103 BGS 10 BLACK LABEL
description: For the majority of Pokemon trainers in the late '90s who started their epic adventure to be the best that ever was Bulbasaur, Charmander, and Squirtle along with their final forms of Venusaur, Charizard, and Blastoise hold special places in their hearts. Being the Pokemon that Professor Oak gave them in Pallet Town, stayed with them all the way through 8 gym challenges throughout Kanto, and culminating with them becoming the Pokemon Champion atop Indigo Plateau, the first-generation starter Pokemon became many children's best friends. Part of the rock-paper-scissor dynamic of these three starter Pokemon was that each of them was stronger against one yet weaker against the other leading to your rival always picking the Pokemon that had an advantage over your own. Featured here is a glorious depiction of one such battle by Ryota Murayama showcasing Venusaur and Charizard squaring off against one another in the most coveted card in the entirety of the Star Birth set. An alternative art card that is sure to stand the test of time among any fans of the original Pokemon Red & Blue Game Boy games, this BGS Black Label example represents the pinnacle of what modern Pokemon has become. You are viewing one of the thousands of items in our 51st Weekly Sunday Auction, spanning all sports and genres, closing on the evening of January 8, 2023. Extended bidding starts at 7:00 p.m. PT. title: 2022 Pokemon SWSH Black Star Promo Quarter Finalist Champions Festival PSA 8
subtitle: PSA Population 1 of 1 - None Graded Higher
description: Held from August 18 to 21, the 2022 Pokemon World Championships were held in London, England at ExCeL London, marking only the second time the world championships were held outside of the United States, and utilizing cards from base Sword & Shield onwards. Given to participants of the tournament, the standard version of the Champion’s Festival promotional card was given out in a set of seven different languages: English, Japanese, French, German, Spanish, Portuguese, and Italian. Illustrated by Naoki Saito, the artwork showcases Sword & Shield starter Pokemon Scorbunny, Sobble, and Grookey riding the London Eye ferris wheel with Pikachu, taking in the historic sights such as Big Ben, with a Galarian Wheezing and Psyduck precariously riding a Corviknight in the background. This particular version was awarded exclusively to the top eight place finishers of each category in the event, with the word quarter-finalist prominently stamped on the card, making this a an extremely difficult version of the card to track down, and a unique collection addition for anyone looking for a piece of Pokemon history.
